==English==

===Interjection===
'''meh...'''

# Expressing [[indifference]] or [[apathy]].
#: ''"What do you want for dinner?" &mdash; "Meh."''
# Expresses confusion; similar to [[what the hell]].
# Means anything that the user wants it to mean. For example: "Yes, No, Maybe, etc..."
# Meh means so much but nothing really.
#: ''Note: Meh is most often used to form a negative or unenthusiastic reply, even if it is meant as "''Yes''".''

----

